<L>__{exterior epps's plantation cotton field day}
<A>__{ july, 1847 the slaves are out working on the field. white hands appear, picking cotton: armsby. he is wholly unskilled at picking cotton, and he puts little effort into the job. as we meet him he seems a decent sort if a little short on self motivation. in anachronistic terminology, he'd be called a "slacker." he joins in with the slaves, singing a spiritual.}
